President Uhuru Kenyatta presided over the Consecration, Presentation and Trooping of the Colours by the 21st Battalion, The Kenya Rifles on Friday. The event took place at Ulinzi Sports Complex in Lang'ata Garrison. Trooping of Color is marked by a parade, march and prayers. It is held to present Presidential and Regimental Colours to an Infantry Unit. This is the last time that President Uhuru graces the trooping. The 21st Battalion was formed in March 2016.